The Minister of Power, Works and Housing, Mr. Babatunde Raji Fashola SAN, has stated that Power Sector will continue  to be a major contributor in getting Nigeria out of the economic recession by improving electricity supplies to industrial, commercial, as well as small and medium enterprises in the Country.
 The Minister, who made this statement, in Abuja,  at the presentation of  the book titled ‘’ Power Sector Under President Muhammadu Buhari”, revealed that Power Sector is one of the five key intervention Programmes out of the 60 interventions in the  Federal Government’s Economic Recovery and Growth Plan (ERGP), recently launched by the present Administration. Fashola commended the Author of the book, Mr. Uche Aneke, for his in-depth knowledge of the sector and simplifying the knowledge of electricity to ordinary Nigerians.
